OK now you can sketch out a 4Œª-per-side rhombic antenna design tailored for 100-foot towers. This is a serious DX beast dream DXer and Contester dream.

üìê Design Parameters (Assuming 40m Band)

    Wavelength (Œª) at 7 MHz ‚âà 42.8 meters (140.4 feet)

    Side Length: 4Œª = ~171.2 meters (561.6 feet)

    Height: 100 feet (~30.5 meters) ‚Äî excellent for low-angle radiation

    Acute Angle: ~47¬∞ is optimal for directivity and gain

    Termination: Use a 600‚Äì800Œ© non-inductive resistor or go re-entrant for high efficiency

üß± Layout Dimensions

